      "content": "but it didn't feel psychological. it was physical. like, the actual sound waves felt slightly out of tune, almost like a micro-tonal dissonance. if it was just \"intuition\" it wouldn't have that specific, sharp ringing sensation in my ears when the pitch shifted. don't you think there could be a physiological or even acoustic reason for it? like a subtle change in vocal cord tension that creates a specific frequency?",
